Date: Fri 2 Dec 2016
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2016; 29(49) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=21643


Foot-and-mouth disease, Guinea-Bissau
-------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 2 Dec 2016 from Dr Bernardo Cassamá, [Directorate General for Livestock, Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development], Bissau, Guinea-Bissau.

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 5 Oct 2016
Date of confirmation of the event: 28 Oct 2016
Date report submitted: 2 Dec 2016
Date of previous occurrence: 2014
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Causal agent: Foot-and-mouth disease virus
Serotype: O, A, SAT1, SAT2
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (2)
Outbreak 1: Cadjito, Cadjito, Bafatá, Bafatá
Date of start of the outbreak: 5 Oct 2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 110 / 75 / 13 / 0 / 0

Outbreak 2: Santanto, Santanto, Bafatá, Bafatá
Date of start of the outbreak: 5 Oct 2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 170 / 18 / 18 / 0 / 0

Summary of outbreaks
Total number of outbreaks: 2
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 280 / 93 / 31 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost
Cattle / 33.21 / 11.07 / 33.33 / 11.07

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or source of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: results obtained for 92 sera and for a pool of 6 vesicular fluids sent to the laboratory:
- antibodies against non-structural proteins detected in 18 sera and confirmed as serotypes O and A (11 animals positive for A and O, 6 animals positive for O and just 1 positive for A)
- SAT1 and SAT2 antigens detected in vesicular fluids. It is impossible to identify how many animals were positive for each serotype.

Control measures
Measures applied: vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists), no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / species / Test / Test date / Results
Senegalese Agricultural Research Institute, Dakar (regional reference laboratory) / Cattle / indirect ELISA / 28 Oct 2016 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-EAFR
<promed-eafr@promedmail.org>

[Antibodies for FMDV serotypes O and A were confirmed. SAT1 and SAT2 antigens were detected as well in vesicular fluids. Further laboratory analysis and virus isolation are required.

Bafatá, the affected region is situated in north-central of Guinea-Bissau. The region is an inland region covered with Savannah or light Savannah woodland and receives an annual rainfall of more than 2000 mm (79 in). Details on the livestock sector of the country can be found at http://www.fao.org/ag/againfo/resources/en/publications/sector_briefs/lsb_GNB.pdf.

Maps of Guinea-Bissau and Bafatá region can be accessed at http://www.nationsonline.org/maps/guinea-bissau-admin-map.jpg and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4678914,12749. - Mod.MMS]
